# Packages
library(dplyr)

library(broom.mixed)
library(lubridate)
# Assume your dataset is df
dat <- df %>%
  mutate(
    topic_cleaned = as.factor(topic_cleaned),
    journal_title = as.character(journal_title)
  )

# Compute HHI of journals within each topic
hhi_by_topic <- dat %>%
  filter(!is.na(topic_cleaned), !is.na(journal_title)) %>%
  count(topic_cleaned, journal_title, name = "n") %>%
  group_by(topic_cleaned) %>%
  mutate(total = sum(n), share = n / total) %>%
  summarise(
    HHI_journal = sum(share^2),
    eff_n_journals = 1 / HHI_journal,
    .groups = "drop"
  )


# Merge back and rescale for interpretability
dat <- dat %>%
  left_join(hhi_by_topic, by = "topic_cleaned") %>%
  mutate(
    SJR_z = as.numeric(scale(SJR)),
    HHI_log = log(HHI_journal),
    eff_n_log = log(eff_n_journals),
    eff_n_journals = eff_n_journals,
    missing_abstract = missing_abstract,
    missing_ref = missing_ref,
  )

# ---- Common cutoff ----
cutoff_date <- as.Date("2025-05-31")

# Helper function to compute follow-up time
# If already cited: use citation time
# If not cited (NA): censor at cutoff - publication_date
get_time <- function(cite_time, pub_date) {
  ifelse(
    is.na(cite_time),
    as.numeric(interval(pub_date, cutoff_date) / months(1)),  # months until cutoff
    cite_time
  )
}
# ---- Rmd cell: utilities (no loops used later) ----
# robust coercion of censor columns to logical (TRUE = censored)
as_censor_logical <- function(x) {
  if (is.logical(x)) return(x)
  if (is.numeric(x)) return(x != 0)
  if (is.factor(x))  x <- as.character(x)
  if (is.character(x)) {
    lx <- tolower(trimws(x))
    return(lx %in% c("true","t","1","yes","y"))
  }
  stop("Unsupported censor type")
}

# build a tidy fixed-effects table from a coxme fit
tidy_coxme <- function(fit) {
  beta <- fixef(fit)
  se   <- sqrt(diag(vcov(fit)))
  tibble(
    term      = names(beta),
    estimate  = as.numeric(beta),
    std.error = as.numeric(se),
    z         = estimate / std.error,
    p.value   = 2 * pnorm(abs(z), lower.tail = FALSE),
    HR        = exp(estimate),
    conf.low  = exp(estimate - 1.96 * std.error),
    conf.high = exp(estimate + 1.96 * std.error)
  )
}

library(dplyr)
library(ggplot2)

# 1) Ensure numeric (silent coercion)
d1 <- d1 %>%
  mutate(
    SJR            = suppressWarnings(as.numeric(as.character(SJR))),
    eff_n_journals = suppressWarnings(as.numeric(as.character(eff_n_journals)))
  )

# 2) Compact robust ranges (595%); widen if collapsed
rng <- function(v) {
  v <- v[is.finite(v)]
  if (!length(v)) return(c(0, 1))
  q <- quantile(v, c(.05, .95), na.rm = TRUE, names = FALSE)
  if (!is.finite(q[1]) || !is.finite(q[2]) || q[1] == q[2]) {
    m <- mean(v); s <- sd(v); if (!is.finite(s) || s == 0) s <- 1
    c(m - s, m + s)
  } else q
}
sjr_r <- rng(d1$SJR)
eff_r <- rng(d1$eff_n_journals)

# 3) Grid (random effect set to 0 by not including it in lp)
grid <- expand.grid(
  SJR            = seq(sjr_r[1], sjr_r[2], length.out = 120),
  eff_n_journals = seq(eff_r[1], eff_r[2], length.out = 120)
)

# 4) Fixed-effects linear predictor for the EXACT fixed part in m1
# m1: Surv(...) ~ SJR * eff_n_journals + (1 | topic_cleaned)
fixed_form <- ~ SJR * eff_n_journals
X    <- model.matrix(fixed_form, data = grid)

beta <- fixef(m1)                  # named vector
idx  <- intersect(colnames(X), names(beta))

lp <- drop(X[, idx, drop = FALSE] %*% beta[idx])
rh <- exp(lp)
rh <- rh / median(rh[is.finite(rh)], na.rm = TRUE)

grid$rh <- rh
grid <- grid[is.finite(grid$rh), ]

# 5) Plot (BIG text)
p <- ggplot(grid, aes(SJR, eff_n_journals, fill = rh)) +
  geom_raster(interpolate = TRUE) +
  geom_contour(aes(z = rh), color = "white", alpha = 0.35, bins = 12) +
  scale_fill_viridis_c(
    breaks = scales::pretty_breaks(n = 4),
    guide = guide_colorbar(
      direction = "horizontal",
      barwidth  = unit(8, "cm"),
      barheight = unit(0.8, "cm")
    )
  ) +
  labs(
    title = "Relative Hazard Surface",
    x = "SJR",
    y = "Effective # of journals (1/HHI)",
    fill = "Rel. hazard"
  ) +
  coord_equal() +  # optional
  theme_minimal(base_size = 24) +
  theme(
    aspect.ratio = 1,

    plot.title   = element_text(size = 30, margin = margin(b = 4)),
    axis.title   = element_text(size = 23),
    axis.text    = element_text(size = 20),

    legend.position = "top",
    legend.direction = "horizontal",
    legend.title = element_text(size = 20),
    legend.text  = element_text(size = 18),
    legend.box.spacing = unit(0.1, "cm"),
    legend.margin = margin(t = 1, b = 1)
  )

print(p)
ggsave("hazard_surface.pdf", p, bg = "white", width = 9, height = 8.5)

library(dplyr)
library(tibble)

# 1) fixed effects coefficients
b <- fixef(m1)

# 2) fixed-effect design matrix 
X <- model.matrix(~ SJR * eff_n_journals + missing_abstract + missing_ref, data = d1)

# 3) per-row contribution by component
needed <- c("SJR", "eff_n_journals", "SJR:eff_n_journals")
stopifnot(all(needed %in% colnames(X)))
stopifnot(all(needed %in% names(b)))

row_terms <- d1 %>%
  transmute(
    topic_cleaned,
    SJR = X[, "SJR"] * b["SJR"],
    eff_n_journals = X[, "eff_n_journals"] * b["eff_n_journals"],
    `SJR:eff_n_journals` = X[, "SJR:eff_n_journals"] * b["SJR:eff_n_journals"]
  )

# 4) aggregate to topic-level 
topic_fixed <- row_terms %>%
  group_by(topic_cleaned) %>%
  summarise(
    SJR = mean(SJR),
    eff_n_journals = mean(eff_n_journals),
    `SJR:eff_n_journals` = mean(`SJR:eff_n_journals`),
    .groups = "drop"
  )

# 5) frailty (random effect)
u_obj <- ranef(m1)$topic_cleaned
frailty_vec <- if (is.matrix(u_obj) || is.data.frame(u_obj)) u_obj[, 1] else as.numeric(u_obj)
topic_vec <- if (!is.null(rownames(u_obj))) rownames(u_obj) else names(u_obj)

topic_re <- tibble(
  topic_cleaned = topic_vec,
  frailty = frailty_vec
)

topic_terms <- topic_fixed %>%
  left_join(topic_re, by = "topic_cleaned")

library(dplyr)
library(tidyr)
library(ggplot2)

plt_signed <- topic_terms %>%
  dplyr::select(topic_cleaned, SJR, eff_n_journals, `SJR:eff_n_journals`, frailty) %>%
  pivot_longer(-topic_cleaned, names_to = "component", values_to = "contribution") %>%
  # global ordering: by total contribution across components
  group_by(topic_cleaned) %>%
  mutate(total = sum(contribution, na.rm = TRUE)) %>%
  ungroup() %>%
  mutate(topic_cleaned = reorder(topic_cleaned, total)) %>%
  # relabel components
  mutate(component = recode(component,
    "frailty" = "Random effect",
    "eff_n_journals" = "# Eff. Journals",
    "SJR:eff_n_journals" = "Interaction",
    "SJR" = "SJR"
  ))

ggplot(plt_signed, aes(x = contribution, y = topic_cleaned, fill = contribution > 0)) +
  geom_col(width = 0.8, show.legend = FALSE) +
  facet_wrap(~ component, nrow = 1, scales = "free_x") +
  geom_vline(xintercept = 0, color = "black") +
  labs(
    title = "",
    x = "Contribution (log-hazard)", y = NULL
  ) +
  theme_minimal(base_size = 20)
